						               													<description>A Panzer Grenadier scenario book featuring 27 scenarios, a campaign game and 102 mounted, laser-cut counters (thinner than die-cut counters but adequate). The scenarios are based on actions of the Panzer Lehr Division on the Western Front between June and November 1944.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The actions, presented in chronological order, begin at Normandy three days after D-Day.  All but the last five are set during the defense of the peninsula and the Allied breakout. The campaign game, also set in Normandy, allows players to fight a series of battles over a period of ten &amp;quot;campaign weeks&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The pieces are elements of the Panzer Lehr Division. Also required for play are pieces and mapboards from other games in the Panzer Grenadier series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
